trans-unit.note:
@TSnatch72 Just to make it clear, yes, this refers to texture surfaces aliasing, not geometry aliasing.

I found a small alternative here: https://forum.wordreference.com/threads/aliasing.1367486/

But it seems that the loanword has won the battle here, for this specific case? I'll keep looking before confirming, as this is the description for the anisotropic texture filtering, an option many people will be using and where using the wrong word might confuse (there are plenty of strings that are confusing enough because of the consequences of the settings, but this should not be one of those).

